description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Clinical Psychologist to join a well-established and supportive Early Intervention in Psychosis Team. The team works with people aged 14 – 65 who have experienced a first episode of psychosis and their carers/families for up to 3 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Covering the diverse inner London Boroughs of Westminster, Kensington and Chelsea the team are recruiting for a dynamic, forward thinking, reliable team member. You will have the opportunity to provide assessment and evidence based CBTp interventions for this client group, including individual, group and family work. Ideally you will have experience of working in a Early Intervention in Psychosis Team or a similar area, with experience in delivering CBTp and Family Interventions for Psychosis, or a willingness to develop these skills through training. You will be familiar with the current standards and targets for the Early Intervention in Psychosis services nationally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to work closely with the multidisciplinary team and offer support and supervision on psychological approaches to working with psychosis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will also include joint managing a caseload of complex clients and providing formal, ongoing clinical supervision and caseload management to other team members as directed by the team manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The trust has strong links with a range of universities, and the post holder will be expected to supervise trainees/students when required. There will be opportunities for professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 24th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Tracy Rawlings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Team Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address tracy.rawlings2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
